
-> Processor: Minimum dual-core CPU (Intel i3 or equivalent) to handle background
monitoring tasks efficiently without slowing down the host system.
-> Memory (RAM): At least 4 GB of RAM to ensure smooth operation alongside other
applications, with higher RAM recommended for systems handling multiple
monitoring modules.
-> Storage: Minimum 100 MB of free disk space for software installation, plus
additional storage for encrypted log files depending on monitoring duration and
intensity. SSD preferred for faster read/write operations.
-> Network Interface: Reliable network adapter (Ethernet or Wi-Fi) to support secure
remote log transmission and real-time alerting.
-> Operating System Compatibility: Hardware must support Windows 10 or later, and
Linux distributions compatible with the suite’s drivers and hooks.
-> Security Hardware (Optional): Trusted Platform Module (TPM) or hardware
encryption support recommended for enhanced data protection.
-> Peripheral Support: Standard keyboard and mouse for input monitoring; optionally
support for webcam or other devices if extended monitoring features are included.

